race.comment: MOTHER GOOSE (11) will relish the sting out of the ground tonight and a senior rider hops aboard. On the quick backup after jumping in trip when a tidy fourth over 1400m at Randwick Kensington. Well placed back to this trip and will be strong late. GUNROOM (6) sent north after the good first-up win, when a fading sixth over 1350m at Doomben. Winning apprentice hops back on and has a good record at this track and trip. Improver. AGENDA SETTER (10) proven fresh performer fitted with the one 900m trial placing at this track. Finds a winnable contest and his best form is usually early in the campaign. MISS SPACEGIRL (8) underrated mare who returned in good order with a fighting victory over 1250m at this track. Goes just as well second-up and will appreciate a bit of sting out of the ground.
